        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "having purchased",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " linen; therefore purchases could be made. This word, and the reason given for Joseph’s haste (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 15:42",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), have, not without a show of reason, been regarded as unintentional evidence in favour of the Johannine Chronology of the Passion. So Meyer, Weiss, and Holtzmann.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καθελὼν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καθαιρεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " was the technical term for taking down from the cross. Proofs in Elsner, Raphel, Kypke, and Loesner.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐνείλησεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": here only in N.T.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν μνημείῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μνήματι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", [161] [162]): no indication in Mk. as in Mt. that it was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "new",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and Joseph’s own.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
