  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "46",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And he bought fine linen",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Thus successful, Joseph purchased fine (probably ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "white",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") linen, the original word for which has been already explained in the note on ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:51",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and then he repaired to Golgotha, where he was joined by Nicodemus, formerly a secret disciple like himself, but whom the Cross had emboldened to come forward and bring ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about an hundred pound weight",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 19:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), to do honour to the Lord of life.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "wrapped him in the linen",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Thus assisted, Joseph took down the Holy Body, laid it in the fine linen, sprinkled the myrrh and aloes amongst the folds, and wound them round the wounded Limbs.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a sepulchre",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] He then conveyed the Body to a new Tomb, wherein as yet no man had ever been laid, and which he had hewn out of the limestone rock in a garden he possessed hard by Golgotha (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 19:41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). He was anxious probably himself to be buried there in the near precincts of the Holy City. Here now they laid the Holy Body in a niche in the rock, and",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "rolled a stone",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] of large size (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 27:60",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") to the horizontal entrance, while",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
